args:
The party defeats Aspidochelone, but the Doctor
escapes. As Aldred moves to pursue him, the
prince looks to help a beleaguered village,
causing them to butt heads. However, it turns
out that the village's troubles were nothing but
a clever trap orchestrated by the Doctor!
We've escaped the space between worlds.
Serves that ugly Aspido-whatever right.\nI'm callin' this a happy ending all around!
Idiot! There's nothing happy about it!
Guess he made like Ranzal's pants\nand split. ...Heh.
I fear it is quite dangerous to leave\nthat man to his own devices.

And yet, we have no idea where he went.
Without more information, we will be
reduced to knocking on every random door
we see and hoping for luck to carry us.
Are you all right? What happened?
W-we're from a nearby village that\nwas suddenly beset by fiends.
I thought we took out all them fiends!
Could the black mana be responsible?
It makes sense—black mana from the tear\nwould likely make fiends run wild!
Well, hell. I thought we had this thing\nall wrapped up with a big pretty bow,\nbut I guess not.
We need to help the villagers.
Do what you want. Go where you want.\nI'm going after the Doctor.
All that matters is seeing my revenge\nfulfilled. Beyond that, I care not who\nlives or dies.
I understand your feelings on the\nSyndicate, but this has to take priority.
No one came for ME when I\nwas begging for help!

My family was murdered in front of me,
my sister was kidnapped, and I was
turned into some kind of lab rat—
AND NO ONE DID ANYTHING!
You have the luxury to save others\nbecause someone is always there\nto save YOU! I don't have that.
Besides, there's no one left I want to save.
All I have is my revenge.
Leave it, boss. Ain't nothin' gonna\nchange this guy's mind.
Fine. But I need to say this...

I'm sorry for saying I understood your
feelings, because it's clear that I don't.
But if you stay on your current path,
all that awaits you is more pain.
Just shut the hell up already.
Are you really okay with this, Aldred?
Oh, this is bad. He must have held\nhis shapeshifted form for too long.
How...am I supposed to sleep...\nwith you screaming in my ear...?
Rrrr! Why do you have to be such a...\nsuch a big obstinate bonehead?!
Those other people may not understand\nyou, but I do! And what happens to me\nif you go and die on me, huh?!
You're right. I'm sorry. But I have no...
Those must be the fiends running amok\nbecause of the black mana!
Why do they have to show up right when\nthis stupid body of mine isn't working?!
Uh, Aldred? There's more. A LOT more.
Andromeda, listen to me. If it looks like\nthe worst is going to happen, I want you\nto leave me and run. You got it? Run.
No! I won't leave you to die!
I won't die. If it comes to that,\nI'll give my body up to the dragon.
But if I have to do that, I'll probably go\nberserk and attack everything—including\nyou. And I...I don't want that to happen.
So please, just do it. Promise to run.
That's a worst-case scenario, and I'm going\nto give everything I have to avoid it. But—
Aldred, wait. Look at the fiends.
Huh? Why aren't they attacking us?\nWhy are they just...leaving?
They're headed toward the village\nthat everyone else went to save!
So that's the game! This wasn't about\nblack mana at all.
It's a trap set by the Doctor to lure in\nall those bleeding hearts!
Aldred, are you actually going to\ngo and save all those people?
If this is the Doctor's doing, he's going\nto be there. That's all I care about.
Your body can't handle a fight right now!
Probably not. But if my time is ending,\nI'll use the last spark of it to scorch\nthe life out of the Doctor!
Don't tell the others about my condition,\nall right? Promise me.
Okay. If that's what you want.
Look out! This is a trap!
Black mana has nothing to do with\nthese fiends—they're under the\ncontrol of the Doctor!
I am very much beginning\nto dislike that man.
Trap or not, the village is under attack.\nWe can't just stand by.
I think we all saw that one comin'.\nRight then, folks! Let's get to work!
I'm only in this for the Doctor.\nThe rest is up to you.
We'll take whatever help we can get\nfor whatever reason we can get it.\nThank you, Aldred.
